metadata.name: Dreaming with Night Terrors
metadata.description:
When you finally go to sleep,
That is where your demons weep.
Lessons come in many shapes,
Many forms in this 'Dreamstate'.

It's not just rainbows, glitter, and roses
It's reflection, no matter the poses.
The ongoing battle of demons within
Acknowledgement, is how you win.

So when you finally go to sleep,
and your demons come out to weep:
Don't pretend they don't exist
'Cause then healing, will resist.

-TM
